column1: #Text=Every day is different , but that ’s the basic schedule .
#Text=What is your main source for political news ?
#Text=Three weekly newsmagazines : The Economist , The Nation , and Science .
#Text=What is your biggest political concern at the moment ?
#Text=In the next 10 years , eliminating governmental deficits , primarily in the United States and in Europe .
#Text=In the next 100 years , dealing with the social and economic consequences of the rise in sea level due to climatic warming .
#Text=How would you assess the presidencies of George W. Bush and Barack Obama ?

#Text=Bush the Younger was unquestionably the most damaging president since FDR , perhaps the most damaging of all time : His " Patriot Act " and other security measures trashed the Constitution , our Constitution .

column1: #Text=His foreign military adventures are the longest wars ever fought by our country .
#Text=Obama was dealt a miserable hand , but even so , I ’m becoming disappointed .
#Text=We still have Bush ’s failure to secure the border with Mexico .
#Text=We still have Bush ’s exporting American jobs overseas .
#Text=Obama did end Bush ’s " global gag rule , " which attempted to prevent family planning agencies all over the world from even discussing abortion .
#Text=And he did make a stab at improving medical care .
#Text=What are your thoughts on Sarah Palin and the Tea Party Movement ?
#Text=Palin was given a job for four years by the voters of Alaska .
#Text=When she got bored with it , she handed the office key to her lieutenant governor and walked away .
#Text=The Tea Party folks are on the right track in trying to get the federal budget deficit under control .
#Text=I fear , though , that they lack the patience and flexibility to do the job gracefully .
#Text=And , they ’re too easily distracted by unrelated issues .
#Text=What is your take on the the health care bill ?
#Text=Obamacare is a step in the right direction , but it leaves intact the private insurance industry , which is a major source of waste .
#Text=We need a public health service , like the one in England .
#Text=What are some of your foreign policy views ?
#Text=America first ! Our unqualified support for Israel is doing us a great deal of damage elsewhere in the world .
#Text=We need to stop all aid , both civilian and military , to Israel until Israel abides by the Oslo Accords .
#Text=We need to stop being the world ’s bully and , instead , lead by example : ratify Kyoto , ratify CEDAW , rein in the international corporations .
#Text=What historical or contemporary figures do you identify with ?
#Text=You know , I think it would be appropriate to name Jimmy Carter .
#Text=I did n’t always agree with what he did , but I could sympathize with why he did it .
#Text=To the extent that any president can be , he was an honest , well-meaning person .
